            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Take ye no thought how, or what thing ye shall answer, or what ye shall say; be not anxiously concerned, neither about the manner, nor the matter of your answer, apology, and defence: in the first part of this clause, the Syriac, Persic, and Ethiopic versions, only read, \"how\"; and the Arabic version only, \"what\";  See Gill on Matthew 10:19. ",
